OL,7,FAhead of Whitelock's outburst, the
OL,8,Fjudge had asked if he wanted a
OL,9,Fbarrister to represent him during the
OL,10,Fsentencing.
OL,12,FThe defendant said: "What's the point?"
OL,14,FDuring the trial, Christopher Rees KC,
OL,15,Fprosecuting, said Whitelock had a long-
OL,16,Fstanding drug addiction and history of
OL,17,Fviolence.
